precautionary_statments_right:
FIRST AID AND PRECAUTIONARY STATEMENTS
This product can cause injury if not handled properly. Use only outdoors or in a well-ventilated area and avoid breathing dusts or mists. Wash face, hands, and any exposed skin thoroughly after handling. Always wear protective gloves, protective clothing, eye protection, and face protection. Do not mix with other household chemicals (such as ammonia, acids, or detergents), as this may produce hazardous gases.
IF IN EYES: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present and easy to do. Continue rinsing.  Get medical attention/advice.
IF ON SKIN (or hair): Remove all contaminated clothing and wash before reuse. Rinse skin with water/shower. If irritation develops seek medical advice.
IF INHALED: Remove person to fresh air and keep comfortable for breathing.  If symptoms persist seek medical attention.
IF SWALLOWED: Rinse mouth. Do not induce vomiting. Immediately call a poison center or doctor.


WARNING -    Causes serious eye and skin irritation..  
KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN AND PETS.

naturestop_precautionary_statement:
Precautionary Statements
CAUTION
Avoid contact with eyes and skin, as irritation may occur. This may cause skin reactions for some people. Not for topical application. Do not ingest. Wash with soap and water after handling and do not use on food and feed commodities.
naturestop_first_aid:
First Aid – Have label/container ready for medical assistance.
IF IN EYES: Hold eye open and rinse with water for 15 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
IF SWALLOWED: Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice. Do not induce vomiting. Rinse mouth with water. Never give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
IF ON SKIN: Wash with soap and water. May cause an allergic reaction. In the case of skin irritation, see a physician.
Contact Poison Control at 1-800-222-1222
The efficacy of this product has not been reviewed by the EPA.
